Igembe North MP Maoka Maore hands over a trophy to the winning team at Laare. [Phares Mutembei, Standard]  Igembe North MP Maoka Maore and former Gatanga MP Peter Kenneth took Raila Odinga’s presidential campaign to Meru.  The leaders who were also in the company of Meru Assembly Speaker Joseph Kaberia were attending the final of a soccer tournament sponsored by Maore at Laare in the vote-rich Igembe region.  Kenneth said he was firmly behind Raila and asked residents to support the former PM's presidential bid. He said he was impressed by how residents of Igembe received Raila during his last visit.  “I know in Igembe North you are for Baba and Azimio la Umoja,” said Kenneth.   He said he was confident Raila had a vision for the country and asked residents to throw their weight behind Raila.  Kenneth who has been touted as a possible running mate for Raila could not be drawn to comment on the issue. The former Gatanga MP said the Mount Kenya region was for Raila.  Maore called for politics devoid of insults, saying politicians should exercise sobriety in their campaigns.     By Moses Nyamori | 2 hours ago By Brian Otieno | 2 hours ago By Patrick Beja | 23 hours ago By Patrick Beja | 1 day ago